thread.title: WikiLeaks declares war on President Trump over his tax returns?!
thread.title_full: WikiLeaks declares war on President Trump over his tax returns?!

author: Greg P.
title: WikiLeaks declares war on President Trump over his tax returns?!
text:
— Ali Vitali (@alivitali) January 22, 2017 
There’s figuratively (and maybe literally) not enough popcorn in all the world if WikiLeaks really means this: Trump Counselor Kellyanne Conway stated today that Trump will not release his tax returns. Send them to: https://t.co/cLRcuIiQXz so we can. 
— WikiLeaks (@wikileaks) January 22, 2017 
They’re responding to Kellyanne Conway saying Sunday morning that the president is “not going to releae his tax returns”: Trump advisor Kellyanne Conway to @ThisWeekABC : Donald Trump "is not going to release his tax returns" https://t.co/l0htGgcvIy pic.twitter.com/5kGSpHf83K 
— ABC News (@ABC) January 22, 2017 
According to WikiLeaks, Trump’s “breach of promise” is “even more gratuitous” than Hillary Clinton hiding the transcript of her Wall Street speeches: Trump's breach of promise over the release of his tax returns is even more gratuitous than Clinton concealing her Goldman Sachs transcripts. 
— WikiLeaks (@wikileaks) January 22, 2017 
Now for the million-dollar question: Is WikiLeaks just playing here or are they serious? This tweet is probably charade but watching the reaction to the inevitable Wikileaks flip to anti-Trump will be hilarious/terrible https://t.co/glRkwU8CQG 
— Tim Miller (@Timodc) January 22, 2017 The Wikileaks call for Trumps taxes isn't surprising, their goal, like Putin, is disrupt and destroy the US. Stop making them a player here 
— Nada Bakos (@nadabakos) January 22, 2017 
To be continued…
